‌Chapter 2 - Just see it‌ Enlightenment is ungraspable, so the more you try to grasp it, Bhagawati, the less it is possible. You cannot hold enlightenment in your fist -- the tighter the fist, the less is the possibility. But you can hold enlightenment in your open hands; that is the only way to hold it.
In your open hands you can hold the whole sky, all the stars, the whole existence, but in your closed fist there is nothing.

